@adoroszlai thanks... this is pretty frustrating. I am thinking about disabling that test.  There is no obvious reason for the NPE. I put an assert checking for null on that `handle` variable.  So where is the NPE?

```
java.lang.NullPointerException
	at org.apache.ambari.server.agent.TestHeartbeatHandler.testComponents(TestHeartbeatHandler.java:1355)
```

The line is

```
ComponentsResponse actual = handler.handleComponents(DummyCluster);
```

I suspect that if the NPE was in `handleComponents`, the indicated line would be different.   Any thoughts on this? Could it be an odd injection scenario?

@aonishuk  and @adoroszlai  
This is a much needed fix, thank you. 

I am running into exactly this issue with my ambari-agents locking up after being up for a while. I spent several hours reading the Ambari source code and tracked down this very issue to exactly the problem you identified. Subprocesses launched by `resource_management.core.shell.py` will hang with no CPU activity, but running the very same command manually will execute normally. The subprocess buffers for STDOUT and STDERR are too small for the output generated by some of the subprocess commands. 

When will this fix be scheduled for release?
